  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments for creating a customized typeface instance from a variable or color font.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` carries the parameters used when calling <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone> to produce a specific variant of a typeface. This includes selecting the font collection index, the color palette index, palette color overrides, and the variation axis coordinates.

This is a `ref struct` and cannot be stored on the heap or across await boundaries.

## Examples

```csharp
var coords = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
{
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700 },
};
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    VariationDesignPosition = coords,
};
using var typeface = original.Clone(args);
```
]]></format>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
